<formulas>
    <formula>
        <given>
            <rootComponent name="S" type="Solution"/>
            <component name="X" type="Solute" of="S"/>
        </given>

        <requires>
            <data>X.mass</data>
            <data>S.volume</data>
        </requires>

        <compute how="inline" what="X.matterQuantityConcentration">X.mass/S.volume</compute>
    </formula>

    <!--
    The question is thus : how to store complicated formulas, just like 12 -> 1s2,2s2,2p4,3p2,3s2 ??
    And the answer is : we can't
    So how about adding an how=(inline|<link>) attribute to the <compute> tag in order to link kotlin code to formulas ?
    -->

    <!--
    Another important problem : if we store physical elements as json-notated objects (which should be no big deal),
    how to link them to words ? how to process them accordingly ?
    I think here again is hybridisation the solution : link xml elements to real kotlin code.
    -->
</formulas>
